Two detectives followed the suspect and found him walking to Deet's house in Blackburn and putting drugs in a black golf glove with a 60% purity underneath the lawyer's trash cans.
Shortly after the transfer, Scarborough was repeatedly called by Ditto, who was at a dinner at the Iwood Park football stadium of the Blackburn Rovers team.
The lawyer came home for the drugs; there were nine conversations between them.
The court learned that Ditt was a regular user of cocaine after tests found traces of the Class A drug in his hair, his wallet and his credit cards.
