It will be recalled that three years ago on December 11th, a spontaneous nationalist rally took place in Manezhya Square, which turned into mass riots.
Levada Center also asked Russians what holiday is celebrated on November 4.
In two years, the number of those who know the correct answer (People's Unity Day) has increased from 41% to 49%.
However, only 15% of the population attends the festivities.
About the same number (17%) are willing to celebrate the October Revolution Day on November 7.
