Moreover, we will buy and - let's not kid ourselves - eat 90 million pounds of chocolate on Halloween.
The one thing we don't want to eat is candy in the form of cornflakes; and yet, according to the National Pastry Association, nearly 35 million pounds of it is sold on Halloween.
That's about nine billion individual corn kernels.
It's a mystery I have yet to unravel.
Nothing says Halloween like a haunted house.
They have amazing names, like "Fear Behind Walls" (which is actually a prison, by the way), "Wow and Scream" and "Shock House".
