Roman Senchin is the undisputed leader of the generation of today's thirty- and forty-year-old novelists.
Almost every publication of his tough, built on the material of modern life stories and novels causes heated debates among critics of various trends.
It can be argued that the articles about Senchin's prose and publicity, the reviews of his books and the magazine publications put together create a curious and unexpected landscape of Russian literature from the late 1990s to the early 2010s.
In the debates about the works of "one of the most controversial modern writers", in the words of the critic Sergei Chuprinin, the discussion is mostly about what its participants understand by the word "literature", what they see as the present and the future not only of our literature, but also of life.
